column5: Beauty weekend were having. Got to my spot by 4:30 am. Ya couldnt sleep with this spring type weather. Got me all giddy like. Fresh fish and sweet tater fries for dinner.
You are the man. I'm eating fish too now! Salmon, trout, Talapia. . .  It comes cleaned and filleted.  Hwy robbery I say! Good going B, just don't ' drop' in on them lol

Hey Brian,  good work on the whities. How was the slush and ice thickness? Thinking of taking the atv for the first time tomorrow but can't get solid info on what to expect for ice thickness and slush?  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
VERY NICE Mr B!  And you are getting SO good at the pan flute for the musical intro too...
Nice bri!!  Make sure to leave a few cigar butts behind so I can find the exact spot tomorrow!!!!
Nice whitie Brian love the flute playing you were doing while fishing;>)

Nice bri!!  Make sure to leave a few cigar butts behind so I can find the exact spot tomorrow!!!! No, we all clean those up, it's the blood spots beside the 'skim over hole' is the key in that area Nick

Way to go Bro. I gots to get back up there one last time, you gave me the itch. Just got back from a Ice bungalow trip on Nipissing, 4 guys in a 8 man, 3 nights 4 days. 31 Walleye, 8 Perch, 1 Pike. Were already talking doing it again next year.
Nice fish Brian. Thanks for sharing the video.
AWESOME BRIAN!  I'm exactly the same way before a day fishing, toss and turn then screw it...I'm outta here....lol.

Thanks fellas.  Was out set up at 5:30. Not sure why,as I cant seem to get anything at dark, but mark a whole lot of fish. Maybe if I used live bait,I might get something, but I dont so I just enjoy my coffee and toast til go time.LOL  Walking was a breeze today,so moved around alot. Started in 45 fow and my last spot was 32 fow. Some perch,herring and another huge whitie that unbutton at the hole. Didnt have time to reach the cam, as it came up quicker then the one yesterday.  Nice bri!!Make sure to leave a few cigar butts behind so I can find the exact spot tomorrow!!!!   You get lost????????????? LMAO  Way to go Bro. I gots to get back up there one last time, you gave me the itch. Just got back from a Ice bungalow trip on Nipissing, 4 guys in a 8 man, 3 nights 4 days. 31 Walleye, 8 Perch, 1 Pike. Were already talking doing it again next year.  Lets getater bro
